# Hammerspoon Implementation Rules

- Prefer extending an existing module only when the new behavior clearly belongs there.
- Otherwise create a new module under `modules/` and wire it through repo `init.lua`.
- Module disablement must be safe: disabling a module should remove its commands and hotkeys cleanly.
- Keep launcher action wiring in repo `init.lua` unless a clear abstraction improves maintainability.
- Keep visual launcher changes inside `assets/launcher.html` whenever possible.
- Keep keyboard navigation working after UI changes.
- Preserve `Cmd + Shift + Space` as the launcher entry unless the user explicitly changes the requirement.
- Avoid introducing new runtime persistence files into the repo.

# Verification Expectations

- After code changes, reload Hammerspoon.
- Sanity check launcher open behavior.
- Sanity check affected hotkeys or actions.
- If a module was changed, verify its enable/disable path still behaves correctly.
